DOCUMENT();
############################################################ # Load Macros ############################################################ loadMacros( "PGstandard.pl", "PGML.pl", "AnswerFormatHelp.pl", "niceTables.pl", "parserRadioButtons.pl", "PGcourse.pl", ); COMMENT('Authored in PreTeXt');
############################################################ # Header ############################################################ TEXT(beginproblem());
############################################################ # PG Setup Code ############################################################ Context("LimitedNumeric"); $yesno=RadioButtons([ "So 2 is a solution to this inequality.", "So 2 is not a solution to this inequality.", ], 0, showInStatic => 0 );
############################################################ # Body ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML Is [`2`] a solution to the inequality [`\newcommand{\lt}{<}\frac{z+3}{z-1}\lt\sqrt{18z}\text{?}`]
>> [@DataTable( [ [PGML('[`\dfrac{z+3}{z-1}`]'), PGML('[`{}\lt{}`]'), PGML('[`\sqrt{18z}`]'), ], [PGML('[_]{5}{2}'), PGML('[`{}\wonder{\lt}{}`]'), PGML('[_]{6}{2}'), ], ], align => 'rcl', valign => 'middle',);@]* <<
[_]{$yesno}{5}
END_PGML
############################################################ # Solution ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION We have to substitute [`2`] in for [`z`] and simplify each side:
[```\newcommand{\highlight}[1]{\mathchoice{\colorbox{lightsapphire}{$\displaystyle #1$}}{\colorbox{lightsapphire}{$\textstyle #1$}}{\colorbox{lightsapphire}{$\scriptstyle #1$}}{\colorbox{lightsapphire}{$\scriptscriptstyle #1$}}}\newcommand{\substitute}[1]{{\color{blue}{{#1}}}}\newcommand{\confirm}[1]{\stackrel{\checkmark}{#1}}\newcommand{\wonder}[1]{\stackrel{\text{?}}{#1}}\newcommand{\lt}{<}\newcommand{\amp}{&} \begin{aligned} \frac{z+3}{z-1}\amp\lt\sqrt{18z}\\ \frac{\substitute{2}+3}{\substitute{2}-1}\amp\wonder{\lt}\sqrt{18(\substitute{2})}\\ \frac{\highlight{5}}{\highlight{1}}\amp\wonder{\lt}\sqrt{\highlight{36}}\\ \highlight{5}\amp\confirm{\lt}\highlight{6} \end{aligned} ```]
Since [`\newcommand{\lt}{<}5\lt6`] is true, [`2`] is indeed a solution to this inequality.
END_PGML_SOLUTION
